## **Task 12: Debugging Exercise**

**Objective:** Find and fix link and image errors.

**Instructions:**

Copy this code into `debug-links.html` and fix all **10 errors**:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Debug Practice</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <img src="logo.png" alt=>
        <h1>My Website</h1>
    </header>
    
    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="home.html">Home</a>
            <li><a href="about.html">About</a></li>
            <li><a ="contact.html">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
    
    <main>
        <section id="welcome>
            <h2>Welcome</h2>
            <p>Check out our <a href="#services>services</a>.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section id="services">
            <h2>Our Services</h2>
            <img src="images/service.jpg" width="300" height="200" />
        </section>
        
        <section>
            <h2>Contact</h2>
            <p>Email: <a href="info@example.com">info@example.com</a></p>
            <p>Phone: <a href="tel:555-1234">555-1234</a></p>
        </section>
    </main>
    
    <footer>
        <p><a href="#top">Back to Top</a></p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

**Questions to Answer:**
1. List all errors found
2. What are the corrected versions?
3. Which errors would prevent links from working?
4. Which errors would prevent images from displaying?
5. Which errors are accessibility issues?

---

## **Common Mistakes to Avoid**

- Forgetting alt attributes on images
- Using vague alt text like "image" or "photo"
- Writing "click here" instead of descriptive link text
- Forgetting to close anchor tags
- Using wrong quote marks around attributes
- Incorrect file paths for images
- Not using proper international format for phone links
- Forgetting character entity semicolons
- Using spaces in filenames or URLs
- Not testing links before submitting

---

## **Best Practices Review**

**Images:**
- ✓ Always include alt attribute
- ✓ Use descriptive, specific alt text
- ✓ Optimize image file sizes
- ✓ Use appropriate image formats
- ✓ Include width and height when known

**Links:**
- ✓ Use descriptive link text
- ✓ Test all links
- ✓ Use relative paths for internal links
- ✓ Open external links in new tabs
- ✓ Indicate when links open new windows

**Accessibility:**
- ✓ Provide meaningful alternative text
- ✓ Write self-explanatory link text
- ✓ Define abbreviations
- ✓ Ensure keyboard navigation works
- ✓ Use semantic HTML

